Class EarthServerGenericClient.Model_WCPSDemWCS


Extends EarthServerGenericClient.AbstractSceneModel.
Scene Model: WCPS Image with DEM from WCS Query 2 URLs for the service, 2 Coverage names for the image and dem.
Defined in: Module_WCPSDemWCS.js.

createModel(root, cubeSizeX, cubeSizeY, cubeSizeZ)
Creates the x3d geometry and appends it to the given root node. This is done automatically by the SceneManager.
Parameters:
root
- X3D node to append the model.
cubeSizeX
- Size of the fishtank/cube on the x-axis.
cubeSizeY
- Size of the fishtank/cube on the y-axis.
cubeSizeZ
- Size of the fishtank/cube on the z-axis.
receiveData(data)
This is a callback method as soon as the ServerRequest in createModel() has received it's data. This is done automatically.
Parameters:
data
- Received data from the ServerRequest.

value

setSpecificElement(element)
Every Scene Model creates it's own specific UI elements. This function is called automatically by the SceneManager.
Parameters:

setURLs(wcpsurl, demurl)
Sets the url for both the WCPS and WCS Queries.
Parameters:
wcpsurl
- Service URL for the WCPS Request
demurl
- Service URL for the WCS Request
setWCPSQuery(querystring)
Sets a complete custom querystring.
Parameters:
querystring
- the querystring. Use $CI (coverageImage), $CD (coverageDEM), $MINX,$MINY,$MAXX,$MAXY(AoI) and $RESX,ResZ (Resolution) for automatic replacement. Examples: $CI.red , x($MINX:$MINY)
setWCSVersion(version)
Sets the WCS Version for the WCS Query String. Default: "2.0.0"
Parameters:
version
- String with WCS version number.
